## 🎯 objective

- Introduce Henrik as the founder
- Build excitement around the launch of Vorker.ai
- Show how the product helps small businesses execute faster
- Drive curiosity and clicks

---

## 🎥 video format

**1. talking head (primary)**

- Henrik speaking directly to camera
- Confident, natural, founder energy
- Conversational, not overly scripted

**2. platform visuals (supporting)**

- Clean screen recordings / UI clips of Vorker.ai
- Intercut throughout (not one long block)
- Focus on: actions, flows, and outcomes

---

## ⚡ tone & style

- Fast-paced, modern, high-energy
- Human and relatable
- Slightly playful
- Clean startup aesthetic

👉 This should feel like a **scroll-stopping LinkedIn/TikTok hybrid**, not a corporate product video.

---

## ✨ editing & text style (key section)

**kinetic typography (required):**

- Text synced to Henrik’s speech
- Highlight key phrases:
  - “work smarter”
  - “get things done”
  - “connected to your business”
  - “less busywork”

**caption rules:**

- Do NOT caption full sentences
- Use short punchy phrases (3–5 words max)
- Highlight only key words
- Keep text moving (pop, slide, snap)

**general editing style:**

- Quick cuts (every ~1–2 seconds where appropriate)
- No dead air
- Keep visual momentum throughout
- Subtle zooms and movement on talking head

---

## ⏱️ length

- Max: 60 seconds
- Ideal: ~45–60 seconds

---

## 🧩 structure (guideline)

**hook (0–5 sec)**

Strong, curiosity-driven opening

→ Example direction: overwhelm, too many tools, nothing getting done

**intro (5–15 sec)**

Henrik introduces himself + Vorker

**problem + shift (15–30 sec)**

Shift from “more tools” → “actual execution”

**product (30–50 sec)**

Introduce Vorker.ai

Show:

- connections to tools
- real actions / workflows
- execution (not just ideas)

**CTA (last 5–10 sec)**

Encourage viewers to check out Vorker.ai

---

## 🎬 editor execution notes (super important)

**pacing:**

- Average cut every 1–2 seconds
- Avoid long static shots
- Energy should build, not drop

**platform visuals:**

- Only clean, intentional UI moments
- Highlight actions (clicks, flows, results)
- Use zooms to guide focus

**music:**

- Modern, light hype / startup energy
- Not cinematic
- Not corporate
- Should support momentum, not overpower

**subtitles:**

- Burned-in
- Clean and readable
- Designed for “watching without sound”

👉 If someone watches muted, they should still understand the core idea.

---

## 🎨 visual elements

- Lower third: “Henrik – Founder, Vorker”
- Smooth transitions
- Clean UI highlights
- Subtle motion throughout

